---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { PaletteDemo } from '../components/PaletteDemo';

const DOWNLOAD_URL = 'https://github.com/andydev404/cleft/releases/latest';
const REPO_URL = 'https://github.com/andydev404/cleft';
---

<Layout
  title="Cleft — the clipboard manager for macOS that remembers everything"
  description="Your Mac's clipboard holds one item. Cleft keeps everything you copy — searchable, organized, and stored only on your Mac. Free, open source, no account."
>
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="wrap nav-inner">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="5" fill="#4f7dff" />
          <path d="M12 3v6l2.5-2L17 9V3" fill="#0d1117" />
        </svg>
        Cleft
      </a>
      <a class="nav-link optional" href="#features">Features</a>
      <a class="nav-link optional" href="#privacy">Privacy</a>
      <a class="nav-link" href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      <a class="btn btn-primary btn-small" href={DOWNLOAD_URL} rel="noopener">Download</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <header class="wrap hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow" data-hero>Free & open source · macOS</p>
      <h1 data-hero>
        Your Mac forgets what you copy. <em>Cleft doesn't.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub" data-hero>
        Every copy overwrites the last one — the address, the code, the color you needed again ten
        minutes later. Cleft keeps them all. Press <kbd>⌘</kbd><kbd>⇧</kbd><kbd>V</kbd> anywhere and
        <strong>everything you've ever copied is right there</strong> — searchable, organized, and
        stored only on your Mac.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-ctas" data-hero>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={DOWNLOAD_URL} rel="noopener">Download for macOS</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">Read the source</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-fineprint" data-hero>
        <b>Free forever.</b> MIT licensed · No account · No telemetry
      </p>
    </div>
    <PaletteDemo client:load />
  </header>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="pain-title">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
        <h2 id="pain-title">You've already lost things today.</h2>
        <p>
          The system clipboard has held exactly one item since 1984. Every copy quietly destroys the
          previous one — you only notice when it's the one you needed.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-grid">
        <div class="pain-card" data-reveal>
          <span class="mono"><s>the address you typed out</s> → 284916</span>
          <p><b>The 2FA code</b> that just overwrote the address you spent a minute writing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-card" data-reveal>
          <span class="mono">#4F7D… <s>#4F7Dsomething?</s></span>
          <p><b>Tuesday's hex color.</b> You had it. It was perfect. It's gone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-card" data-reveal>
          <span class="mono">docker compose up -d --build ×9</span>
          <p><b>The same command,</b> re-found and re-copied for the ninth time today.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="features" aria-labelledby="features-title">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
        <h2 id="features-title">One shortcut. Your whole copy history.</h2>
        <p>
          Cleft is a floating palette, not another window to manage. It shows up over whatever
          you're doing, hands you the clip, and gets out of the way.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature" data-reveal>
          <h3>Find it by typing anything</h3>
          <p>
            Full-text search across everything you've copied — filter by app, type, tag, or
            collection. No mouse required for any of it.
          </p>
          <div class="feature-demo"><span class="chip">app:figma</span><span class="chip">type:color</span><span class="chip">#brand</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" data-reveal>
          <h3>It knows what you copied</h3>
          <p>
            Colors get swatches. JSON gets a collapsible tree. SQL, Markdown, URLs, file paths —
            each clip is detected and previewed as what it is.
          </p>
          <div class="feature-demo">
            <span class="badge" style="color:#4f7dff;background:rgba(79,125,255,.12)">COLOR</span>
            <span class="badge" style="color:#e0a23c;background:rgba(224,162,60,.12)">SQL</span>
            <span class="badge" style="color:#b06cff;background:rgba(176,108,255,.12)">JSON</span>
            <span class="badge" style="color:#46b29d;background:rgba(70,178,157,.12)">CODE</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" data-reveal>
          <h3>It remembers where, too</h3>
          <p>
            Every clip keeps its source — the app, the window, the URL it came from. "That thing I
            copied from the Stripe docs" is a real search.
          </p>
          <div class="feature-demo"><span class="chip">Safari · stripe.com/docs</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" data-reveal>
          <h3>Rules that file it for you</h3>
          <p>
            IF a clip comes from Figma, THEN put it in Brand Colors. Automation runs at capture
            time, before you've even opened the palette.
          </p>
          <div class="feature-demo"><span class="chip chip-if">IF app == "Figma"</span><span class="chip chip-then">THEN → Brand Colors</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" data-reveal>
          <h3>Secrets never get saved</h3>
          <p>
            Password-manager output, API keys, one-time codes, card numbers — detected and refused
            at capture. Not hidden. Never written to disk at all.
          </p>
          <div class="feature-demo"><span class="chip chip-blocked">eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs…</span><span class="chip">not stored</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" data-reveal>
          <h3>Work and life, separated</h3>
          <p>
            Workspaces keep client work, personal projects, and everything else in their own
            histories. Pin what matters; it never ages out.
          </p>
          <div class="feature-demo"><span class="chip">● Personal</span><span class="chip">Work</span><span class="chip">★ pinned</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="privacy" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
    <div class="wrap privacy">
      <div class="section-head" style="margin-bottom:0" data-reveal>
        <h2 id="privacy-title">A clipboard manager sees everything you copy. That's why this one tells no one.</h2>
        <p>
          Most clipboard tools ask you to trust a privacy policy. Cleft asks you to read the code —
          audit the capture pipeline line by line before you let it watch anything.
        </p>
      </div>
      <ul class="privacy-list">
        <li data-reveal>
          <span class="privacy-check">✓</span>
          <span><b>100% local.</b> Your history is a SQLite file in your own Library folder. Nothing is uploaded, ever.</span>
        </li>
        <li data-reveal>
          <span class="privacy-check">✓</span>
          <span><b>Zero network calls at capture.</b> Copying never triggers a request — no favicon fetches, no analytics, no telemetry.</span>
        </li>
        <li data-reveal>
          <span class="privacy-check">✓</span>
          <span><b>No account. No sign-up.</b> Download, press <kbd>⌘</kbd><kbd>⇧</kbd><kbd>V</kbd>, done.</span>
        </li>
        <li data-reveal>
          <span class="privacy-check">✓</span>
          <span><b>Open source, MIT.</b> The capture pipeline, the secret detection, all of it — <a href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">public on GitHub</a>.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-final">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 data-reveal>The next thing you copy is worth keeping.</h2>
      <p data-reveal>Thirty seconds from download to your first rescued clip. Free, open source, and it never leaves your Mac.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas" data-reveal>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={DOWNLOAD_URL} rel="noopener">Download Cleft for macOS</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">Star on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="wrap footer-inner">
      <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Cleft · MIT License</span>
      <span>
        <a href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">GitHub</a> ·
        <a href={`${REPO_URL}/issues`} rel="noopener">Report an issue</a> ·
        <a href={`${REPO_URL}/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md`} rel="noopener">Contribute</a>
      </span>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<script>
  import gsap from 'gsap';
  import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger';

  if (!window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
    gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

    gsap.from('[data-hero]', {
      opacity: 0,
      y: 22,
      duration: 0.7,
      stagger: 0.09,
      ease: 'power2.out',
    });

    for (const el of document.querySelectorAll('[data-reveal]')) {
      gsap.fromTo(
        el,
        { opacity: 0, y: 26 },
        {
          opacity: 1,
          y: 0,
          duration: 0.65,
          ease: 'power2.out',
          scrollTrigger: { trigger: el, start: 'top 86%', once: true },
        }
      );
    }
  } else {
    for (const el of document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-reveal]')) el.style.opacity = '1';
  }
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* Palette demo (PaletteDemo.tsx) */
  .pd {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 14px;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .pd-slot {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border: 1px dashed var(--line-2);
    border-radius: 11px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  .pd-slot-label {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    font-size: 10.5px;
  }

  .pd-slot-value {
    color: var(--muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
    min-width: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .pd-slot-note {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--amber);
  }

  .pd-window {
    border: 1px solid var(--line-2);
    border-radius: 18px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--panel) 88%, transparent);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    box-shadow: 0 28px 70px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .pd-search {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    color: var(--faint);
    font-size: 13.5px;
  }

  .pd-search span:nth-child(2) {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .pd-kbd {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 2px 7px;
  }

  .pd-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
    padding: 8px;
    min-height: 232px;
  }

  .pd-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 9px 10px;
    border-radius: 9px;
  }

  .pd-row:first-child {
    background: rgba(79, 125, 255, 0.1);
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(79, 125, 255, 0.25);
  }

  .pd-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
    border-radius: 7px;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .pd-preview {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--paper);
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
  }

  .pd-badge {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border: 1px solid;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }

  .pd-footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  .pd-dot {
    color: #46b29d;
    font-size: 8px;
    vertical-align: 1px;
  }
</style>
